{"parse":{"title":"Encyclopedia of Women and Islamic Cultures","pageid":14649009,"revid":851434158,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <i><b>Encyclopedia of Women and Islamic Cultures</b></i> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Reference_work\" title=\"Reference work\">reference work</a> on <a href=\"/wiki/Gender_studies\" title=\"Gender studies\">gender studies</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_world\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Islamic world\">Islamic world</a>. This <a href=\"/wiki/Encyclopedia\" title=\"Encyclopedia\">encyclopedia</a> is aimed at becoming \"an essential reference work for students and researchers in the fields of gender studies, <a href=\"/wiki/Middle_Eastern_studies\" title=\"Middle Eastern studies\">Middle Eastern</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Islamic_studies\" title=\"Islamic studies\">Islamic studies</a>, as well as scholars of <a href=\"/wiki/Religion\" title=\"Religion\">religion</a>, history, politics, anthropology, geography and related disciplines.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Brill_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Brill-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>The six-volume encyclopedia is the result of collaboration of over 1,000 scholars from around the world. It was published from 2003 to 2007.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Brill_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Brill-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Encyclopedia_of_Women_and_Islamic_Cultures&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Encyclopaedia_of_Islam\" title=\"Encyclopaedia of Islam\">Encyclopaedia of Islam</a></i></li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Encyclopaedia_of_the_Qur%27an\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Encyclopaedia of the Qur&#39;an\">Encyclopaedia of the Qur'an</a></i></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Encyclopedia_of_Women_and_Islamic_Cultures&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Brill-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Brill_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Brill_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.brill.nl/default.aspx?partid=18&amp;pid=23689\">\"Encyclopedia of Women &amp; Islamic Cultures\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2007-12-10</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Encyclopedia+of+Women+%26+Islamic+Cultures&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.brill.nl%2Fdefault.aspx%3Fpartid%3D18%26pid%3D23689&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEncyclopedia+of+Women+and+Islamic+Cultures\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Encyclopedia_of_Women_and_Islamic_Cultures&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.brill.nl/default.aspx?partid=18&amp;pid=23689\"><i>Encyclopedia of Women and Islamic Cultures</i> at Brill publishers</a></li></ul>\n<p><br